    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train -
        Recondition - Inspect and Measure Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Inspect and Measure Valves</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s1321" count="1">Remove carbon deposits from valve stems and valve heads.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect each valve for burn marks, warpage, scuffing, and bending. Replace any damaged
                valves.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect valve stem tip for scoring, pitting, or signs of excessive wear.
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_325.xml" xrefid="s1322.2">Reface valve stem tip</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s1322.2"/>
                or replace valve if required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350013375" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/eg8590.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Measure valve stem diameter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Two measurements 90 degrees apart</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Three valve stem diameter measurement locations</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure valve stem diameter with a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_341.xml" xrefid="t335001303">micrometer</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001303"/>
                at three locations. At each location, take two measurements 90 degrees apart. Average the two
                measurements from each location.
            </para>
            <para>If the average of measurements at any of the three locations is not within valve stem diameter
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_339.xml" xrefid="t335001301">Specification</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001301"/>, replace that valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Determine valve stem-to-guide running clearance using the valve stem diameter measurements
                above and
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_322.xml" xrefid="s1319">valve guide inside diameter measurements</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s1319"/>. Subtract the average valve stem diameter from the average valve guide inside
                diameter.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Valve Stem-to-guide Running Clearance = Valve Guide Inside Diameter - Valve Stem Diameter
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace valve or valve guide if not within
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_339.xml" xrefid="t335001301">Specifications</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001301"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
